LLM Response 3: "Absolutely — this new requirement changes the meaning of “feasible.”

Updated behavior

Allocation is feasible only if:

All requests can be satisfied without exceeding any capacity, and

At least one resource has leftover capacity after satisfying all requests (i.e., not all resources are fully consumed).

So if requests exactly consume every resource’s full capacity, the function must return False.

